00:40:46,710 --> 00:40:49,649
Speaker 1: I think someone needs to make some sort of epic versus Shmoop for the DS.

659
00:40:49,890 --> 00:40:52,930
Speaker 1: Some sort of Wi-Fi enabled leaderboard rankings.

660
00:40:53,978 --> 00:40:54,469
Speaker 1: I can dream.

661
00:40:55,150 --> 00:40:59,549
Speaker 0: So if you had to pick one Shmoop forever, Giga Wing, Giga Wing, Giga Wing.

662
00:40:59,850 --> 00:41:00,050
Speaker 1: All right.

663
00:41:00,350 --> 00:41:00,634
Speaker 1: I think.

664
00:41:00,755 --> 00:41:01,990
Speaker 1: or after Call of the Shadows.

665
00:41:02,030 --> 00:41:06,190
Speaker 0: Yeah, I think I would just pick Galaga one because Galaga.

666
00:41:06,731 --> 00:41:10,989
Speaker 0: The thing is, Galaga is actually a really interesting game that people don't seem to fully understand.

667
00:41:11,550 --> 00:41:14,550
Speaker 0: Galaga, you're a little ship at the bottom and there's bad guys at the top.

668
00:41:15,170 --> 00:41:17,550
Speaker 0: And it's not like Galaxian or Space Invaders.

669
00:41:17,690 --> 00:41:19,810
Speaker 0: So the bad guys are there when you start the level.

670
00:41:20,270 --> 00:41:24,710
Speaker 0: The bad guys fly into the screen one row at a time.

671
00:41:25,091 --> 00:41:28,810
Speaker 0: So it's like you're sitting there with a blank slate and a row of bad guys comes in.

672
00:41:29,011 --> 00:41:39,150
Speaker 0: While they're coming in, if you position yourself properly, you can kill all or a lot of them very quickly because they're all in a line and they all follow the same path.

673
00:41:39,290 --> 00:41:43,370
Speaker 0: So if you shoot at the right spot in their path, you can hit a lot of them with bullets.

674
00:41:44,150 --> 00:41:46,489
Speaker 0: Then whichever ones remain alive line up at the top.

675
00:41:47,090 --> 00:41:54,809
Speaker 0: And after all the bad guys come in, they sort of go back and forth and then they'll take turns diving down at you the same way they do in Galaxian until you kill them all.

676
00:41:55,352 --> 00:41:59,450
Speaker 0: The thing in Galaga that makes it special is the ship capture.

677
00:41:59,910 --> 00:42:08,109
Speaker 0: See, there are these bug bad guys in Galaga and that when they dive down at you, sometimes they'll spray this like wave beam at you.

678
00:42:09,050 --> 00:42:13,929
Speaker 0: And most people go, oh, snaps wave beam and they dodge it or they kill the bad guy that's shooting the wave beam.

679
00:42:14,550 --> 00:42:21,007
Speaker 0: Little do they know, if you have a life remaining and you get hit by the wave beam, you don't die.

680
00:42:21,150 --> 00:42:26,923
Speaker 0: Well, you do die, you lose a life, but it captures your ship and your ship is now a bad guy.

681
00:42:27,571 --> 00:42:31,730
Speaker 0: But when you come back to life, you have a chance to shoot the bad guy.

682
00:42:31,991 --> 00:42:38,610
Speaker 0: And if you do not shoot your ship and you shoot the bad guy, you will now have two ships simultaneously.

683
00:42:38,994 --> 00:42:40,490
Speaker 1: On one hand, double the firepower.

684
00:42:40,793 --> 00:42:42,690
Speaker 1: On the other hand, double the surface area.

685
00:42:42,976 --> 00:42:43,147
Speaker 0: Yep.

686
00:42:43,310 --> 00:42:46,289
Speaker 0: Your ship is now twice as wide as it normally is.

687
00:42:46,611 --> 00:42:50,390
Speaker 0: So it's much harder to dodge things and you basically sacrifice the life.

688
00:42:50,651 --> 00:42:53,890
Speaker 0: But you can shoot two bullets side by side at once.

689
00:42:54,150 --> 00:42:55,270
Speaker 0: And that's crazy awesome.

690
00:42:56,091 --> 00:43:02,770
Speaker 0: So Galaga is actually a very deep game and it plays forever the same way Space Invaders or Galaxian plays forever.

691
00:43:03,510 --> 00:43:04,790
Speaker 0: And it's way cool.

692
00:43:05,071 --> 00:43:05,709
Speaker 0: I like it a lot.

693
00:43:06,231 --> 00:43:06,950
Speaker 0: Yeah, awesome.

